casebody.data:
MIGUEL D. ALDAMA, Appellant, v. FRANCIS F. LASALA, Respondent.

Before Speib and Fbeedman, JJ.

Decided February 7, 1881. Appeal from order of the special term, denying a motion for leave to file and serve exceptions to certain findings of fact of referee nunc pro tunc, after appeal to the court of appeals. Horace Secor, Jr., for appellant. Starr & Hooker, attorneys, and George H. Starr, of counsel, for respondent.

No opinion.

Order affirmed, with costs.
